From November 16, the Ministry of Health announced that a specific group of people who can get booster vaccination there are: people with moderate and severe immunodeficiency; 
people aged 60 years and older who have previously received Sinofarm, Sinovac, and other inactivated vaccines;
healthcare workers are at very high risk of infection and transmission of coronavirus infection; for people recovered from COVID-19 (including previously vaccinated persons). For buffer vaccination, Sputnik-Light will be used, for adolescents - Pfizer, pregnant and lactating women - any of those approved by WHO.

