healthcare workers are at very high risk of infection and transmission of coronavirus infection; for people recovered from COVID-19 (including previously vaccinated persons). For buffer vaccination, Sputnik-Light will be used, for adolescents - Pfizer, pregnant and lactating women - any of those approved by WHO. UPDATE: From December 20, 2021, everyone can get a booster vaccine with Pfizer. UPDATE: The original policy said that announced that a specific group of people who can get a booster vaccination, from December 20, 2021, everyone can get a booster vaccine

Border service of Kyrgystan infomed on April 4, 2020 that different border crossing rules exist for neighbouring countries:  
1)citizens of Kazakhstan who are in the Kyrgyz Republic can only leave through specific checkpoints as Chon-Kapka-road,     Aishabibi-road,  Ak-Tilek-road, KR -   Karasu-road; 
2)  citizens of Uzbekistan who are in the Kyrgyz Republic are allowed to return to Uzbekistan at certain times and in organized groups; 
3) Tajik citizens who are in the Kyrgyz Republic are temporarily unable to enter the Republic of Tajikistan; 
4) no exit options for People Republic of China until further notice
